Introducing Doldol, our miniature miracle!

This little elephant is the smallest orphan to ever come into our care, claiming a title previously held by Ndotto. Her story began on a cold, windy night in northern Kenya, where a newborn elephant was abandoned in the heart of community land. Her mother must have been disturbed during birth and took off into the night, leaving her baby behind.

The deck is stacked against orphaned neonates, but Doldol has been blessed by guardian angels.  First, she had a kind man from the community. He took custody of her for the night, keeping her warm and protected in his boma until our rescue team arrived. 

Then, she had Mishak. Typically, a team of Keepers care for new rescues. However, a calf so small warranted extraordinary measures. Mishak is one of our most gifted and experienced Keepers. He has raised some of our trickiest orphan cases and is the unanimous favourite of any elephant he meets. We knew he would be the perfect ‘parent’ for Doldol. 

And of course, she has you. Your support allows us to provide orphans like Doldol with the specialised, round-the-clock care they need to survive. This #GivingTuesday, your donation or adoption of an orphan like Doldol will automatically be doubled, dollar for dollar. Together, we could raise over one million dollars for conservation today!

To learn more about our matched giving campaign, tap our link in bio/stories or visit: 
sheldrickwildlifetrust.org/campaigns/giving-tuesday

To read Doldol’s full story and watch her rescue video, tap our link in bio/stories or visit:
sheldrickwildlifetrust.org/orphans/doldol 

Thank you, now and always, for your commitment and support.

——

A great story for your weekend!! From @savetheelephants
•
Members of our Samburu team were involved in a nail-biting rescue recently after a bull elephant fell into a septic tank in Samburu National Reserve. The bull, aged in his 30s, crashed through the concrete cover while reaching for an acacia tree and became trapped in neck-deep water for almost 12 hours. 

Fortunately a digger came to the rescue and was able to free the bull from his watery prison. The elephant eventually returned to the bush, shaken but thankfully unharmed. Rescuing elephants from tanks and wells is one of the many challenges we face as more and more human settlements encroach on elephant habitat and conflict cases increase. Save the Elephants is working closely with local authorities and communities in an effort to create a safer landscape for both elephants and people. 

A big asante sana to Moses Lolmodooni, senior warden, Samburu County ranger, as well as the digger owner, Nadeem Omar from Larsen’s Camp (@sunworldsafaris) and brave driver, Mary Huho, who helped rescue the elephant. Watch the dramatic event unfold in this short film. 

Film by @janewynyard/Save the Elephants. Additional footage by @gilbert_sabinga/Save the Elephants.

The touching moment when Wounda the chimpanzee hugs Dr. Jane Goodall in thanks, as she says goodbye. Wounda was nursed back to health from near death by Dr. Goodall and her team. She was released onto their sanctuary islands after being successfully rehabilitated.
This is what wildlife conservation is truly about. Fighting to save and protect those who can’t fight for themselves. Being a voice for the voiceless. Heroes, every one of them.

While the region was devastated from hurricane Ian, the people and the wildlife here are resilient! I am so thankful to SCCF and their efforts to ensure that the next generation inherits a beautiful environment! @sccf_swfl .

Happy Sunday! Thought I’d start your morning off with this delightfully rambunctious bobcat named Andy. Andy’s mom was hit by a car while she was pregnant, before she died, she gave birth to Andy! This adorable bobcat was so small and so fragile, he imprinted on his wildlife rehaber and unfortunately cannot live in the wild. But now he thrives Flamingo Gardens where he is an ambassador animal, teaching everyone on the importance of Florida conservation. Thanks Flamingo Gardens for all your great work with wildlife, if you’re in Florida definitely worth a visit!

Fasten your seatbelts as we rocket to a strange New World with fantastic, alien life beyond our imagination! Better yet, we stay closer to home, on our own planet, diving deep, hundreds of fathoms, to discover the otherworldly tripod fish! Practically blind and void us, distinctive pigments, being it, lives in a world of darkness, and navigates its benthic environment with uniquely adapted, tripod like fins, providing mobility and heighten sensory perception. Incredible footage from: @schmidtocean

The strawberry squid is an absolute stunner, shimmers more than a pair of bedazzled Jordache jeans! Looks more like something you'd find in the  cabinet at Winston's Jewelers, versus an extraordinary under sea creature of stunning beauty! Incredible photograph captured by @paulcaiger #squid #octopus #ocean #marine

A thrilling moment! I might've looked cool, calm and collected on the outside but I was shaking on the inside! Milking a copious glob of deadly venom from a giant fer-de-lance viper in Costa Rica at the Instituto Clodomiro Picado This incredible serpent laboratory creates anti-venom that saves thousands of people every year around the world. They even saved me! Providing me with the anti-venom I needed when I was bitten by a coral snake as a graduate in the jungles of Belize, such a great episode! So much fun!

As @mark.smith.photography powerfully demonstrates in this incredible video, competition between ospreys can be fierce , especially over a delicious fish! In the end, they both emerge from the water with talons tightly entangled but empty of dinner! Congrats Mark on this amazing moment!

I will forever love Pat, the giant pacific octopus! She could be a cheeky cephalopod! Giant in size, heart, and attitude! She gave me a good drenching! A wonderful memory "excuse the colorful blooper" all in good fun. but it's a special moment that I won't forget that I wanted to share! From my dear friends and great advocates for marine conservation @alaskasealifecenter

I find this incredible shot from @benjhicks to be both hopeful and inspirational Despire the vastness of the ocean, this incredible sea turtle takes a deep breath, with courage, and paddles forward! Great shot, Ben! #seaturtle #ocean #marine #conservation

Thanks to all my friends @princesscruises for a smashing Alaskan adventure! I'm having so much fun getting to know all of you, and exploring the wonders of wild Alaska together! I can't believe we sold out the trip! We observed bald eagles and bears feeding on salmon! And now we're about to explore a breathtaking glacier! I look forward to making these great journeys a @princesscruises tradition!

We are wrapping up our incredible @princesscruises journey to Alaska, and I'll never forget working with @alaskasealifecenter amazing marine mammal rescue program. Here is a special memory for me. This adorable, orphaned harbor seal pup will now have a chance to thrive in the majestic wilds of Alaska, thanks to ASLC! This pup is rambunctious, and on its way to recovery, an incredible memory, that warms my heart to know that this young harbor seal had an opportunity to thrive!

Snickers the precocious and adorable porcupine @akwildlife really warmed my heart! Certainly has a robust appetite! Lost its leg, so no longer can survive in the wild, but has educated so many about the amazing life of porcupines! Armed with quills, modified hairs, that will definitely give you a good prick!

Meet Sky, an adorable, orphaned Sitka deer fawn. It's time for me to give her a nice bottle of warm formula, but I thought I'd take a moment to tell you Sky's amazing story! Thankfully Sky was rescued by my friends @akwildlife , she will have a chance to thrive! Alaska is a true wild frontier, but as stewards we must do our best to protect it's many treasures, like adorable Sky!

Incredibly exciting and fascinating captured by @trekkingwithtrevor ! Amazing display of animal behavior. This brawny bruin stands mighty over it it's kill, but the wolf wants a piece of the action! Observe the wolf displaying submissive, almost playful, like behavior to show that the crafty canine is not a threat! But look to your right, and you'll see another wolf sneaking in! Incredible footage Trevor! #bears #wolf #wolves #wilderness #wildlife #nature

Incredible moment captured by wildlife photographer @robertefuller a dedicated kingfisher dad, doting over his clutch! A powerful example of the parental investment found in so many of our fellow earthlings! Great job, Robert! Check out roberts work on YouTube: @RobertEFuller is amazing artwork and photos: robertefuller.com #nature #wildlife #environment

I'm also excited to announce a new nature/adventure to Alaska with @princesscruises for next summer, maybe two! I am so excited! I found out last night, and I couldn't wait to share the news! My friends @marinesanctuaryfdn have been working so hard for this moment. But it's official, the US Senate now recognizes October 23 as National Marine Sanctuary Day! It's incredible, it started way back in 1972 with Congress protecting one square mile of ocean. Today over 600,000 miles of incredible marine habitat, from coast to coast to the great lakes, forever protected for all of us to cherish! So let me be the first to wish you a very happy, national Marine sanctuary day! Sometimes the most incredible natural wonders come the tiniest packages! The Colombian basin, pygmy rabbit, is the rarest bunny in the world! It is also the tiniest. Less than 150 survive today, they've been wiped out because of wildfires and a new virus invading the American west. Thankfully, there is hope. This little critter packs a powerful story! I truly enjoyed making this episode, and I am so thankful to have worked with @usfws and @thewdfw #bunny #bunnies #naturephotography #nature #conservation #endangeredspecies #washingtonstate #adorable
